#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn14.31"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn14.31:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 14 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 14 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn14.31:0.2"
msgid "4. Catutthavagga "
msgstr "4. The Fourth Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 31. Pubbesambodhasutta → pubbasuttaṃ (bj) | pubbe (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn14.31:0.3"
msgid "31. Pubbesambodhasutta "
msgstr "31. Before Awakening "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.170, sc1
msgctxt "sn14.31:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn14.31:1.2"
msgid "“Pubbeva me, bhikkhave, sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato etadahosi: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I thought: "

msgctxt "sn14.31:1.3"
msgid "‘ko nu kho pathavīdhātuyā assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ; "
msgstr "‘What’s the gratification, the drawback, and the escape when it comes to the earth element … "

msgctxt "sn14.31:1.4"
msgid "ko āpodhātuyā assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ; "
msgstr "the water element … "

msgctxt "sn14.31:1.5"
msgid "ko tejodhātuyā assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ; "
msgstr "the fire element … "

msgctxt "sn14.31:1.6"
msgid "ko vāyodhātuyā assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇan’ti? "
msgstr "and the air element?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn14.31:2.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me: "

msgctxt "sn14.31:2.2"
msgid "‘yaṃ kho pathavīdhātuṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ pathavīdhātuyā assādo; "
msgstr "‘The pleasure and happiness that arise from the earth element: this is its gratification. "

#. VAR: yaṃ → yā (si)
msgctxt "sn14.31:2.3"
msgid "yaṃ pathavīdhātu aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā, ayaṃ pathavīdhātuyā ādīnavo; "
msgstr "That the earth element is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback. "

msgctxt "sn14.31:2.4"
msgid "yo pathavīdhātuyā chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ pathavīdhātuyā nissaraṇaṃ. "
msgstr "Removing and giving up desire and greed for the earth element: this is its escape. "

msgctxt "sn14.31:2.5"
msgid "Yaṃ āpodhātuṃ paṭicca … pe … "
msgstr "The pleasure and happiness that arise from the water element … "

msgctxt "sn14.31:2.6"
msgid "yaṃ tejodhātuṃ paṭicca … pe … "
msgstr "The pleasure and happiness that arise from the fire element … "

msgctxt "sn14.31:2.7"
msgid "yaṃ vāyodhātuṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ vāyodhātuyā assādo; "
msgstr "The pleasure and happiness that arise from the air element: this is its gratification. "

msgctxt "sn14.31:2.8"
msgid "yaṃ vāyodhātu aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā, ayaṃ vāyodhātuyā ādīnavo; "
msgstr "That the air element is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback. "

msgctxt "sn14.31:2.9"
msgid "yo vāyodhātuyā chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ vāyodhātuyā nissaraṇaṃ’. "
msgstr "Removing and giving up desire and greed for the air element: this is its escape. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
#. VAR: abhisambuddhoti → abhisambuddho (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn14.31:3.1"
msgid "Yāvakīvañcāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imāsaṃ catunnaṃ dhātūnaṃ evaṃ assādañca assādato ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ na abbhaññāsiṃ, neva tāvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddhoti paccaññāsiṃ. "
msgstr "As long as I didn’t truly understand these four elements’ gratification, drawback, and escape in this way for what they are, I didn’t announce my supreme perfect awakening in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.171, sc4
msgctxt "sn14.31:4.1"
msgid "Yato ca khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imāsaṃ catunnaṃ dhātūnaṃ evaṃ assādañca assādato ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, athāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddhoti paccaññāsiṃ. "
msgstr "But when I did truly understand these four elements’ gratification, drawback, and escape in this way for what they are, I announced my supreme perfect awakening in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn14.31:4.2"
msgid "Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi: "
msgstr "Knowledge and vision arose in me: "

#. VAR: vimutti → cetovimutti (bj, pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn14.31:4.3"
msgid "‘akuppā me vimutti, ayamantimā jāti, natthi dāni punabbhavo’”ti. "
msgstr "‘My freedom is unshakable; this is my last rebirth; now there are no more future lives.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn14.31:4.4"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

